Re: Buying Japanese manga?
by Sairana » Mon 03.15.2010 10:41 pm あいさつ is the noun, as in "a greeting" or "a salutation", not what one says to actually greet someone.--EDIT: Guess this info was already passed along in another thread, but I'll leave it in for posterity. --You should also be made aware that there's no such thing as JLPT lists anymore as far as I am aware. The JLPT has been revamped and they are not making public specific vocabulary/grammar/kanji for the various levels. There's now 5 levels instead of 4 (numbered N5-N1, easiest to hardest).
Sairana
