Re: Buying Japanese manga?
by DevilishMaiden » Tue 07.12.2011 5:30 pm Not sure where you live, but Book Off is a good place to go. The store in NYC has a HUGE selection of manga in Japanese (also a nice selection in English) for just $1 (English a bit more, usually around $5-$7). I also went to their store in Torrance, CA - not as big of a selection in Japanese but it was a very small store. Keep in mind though - a lot are used books in good condition. Unfortunately they don't have any online shop so you'd have to live near a location to have any use of it here's a link to their locations:http://www.bookoffusa.com/?cmd=store#store7
